Updating the docker image on the registry (used by the build jobs):

1. Build the image:
	docker build -t docker.bmw-carit.de/yocto-build .

2. Push to the registry:
	docker push docker.bmw-carit.de/yocto-build


Running a build:

1. Create your fig.yml from the template.
        cp fig.yml.template fig.yml

2. Edit the fig.yml. Make sure that all directories
   you are referring to exist on your host system.

3. Build the container.
        fig build

4. Add the neccessary credentials to ~/.netrc on your host system.
   A preset of technical users is given in .netrc.preset.

5. Run the build command on the image called build.
        fig run build "bitbake <target>"

